        "content": [
          "The genitive case signals possession/belonging.",
          "",
          "ARTICLE CHANGES:      NOM  →  GEN",
          "Masculine:            der  →  des",
          "Feminine:             die  →  der",
          "Neuter:               das  →  des",
          "Plural:               die  →  der",
          "",
          "Genitive 'des' needs agreement from the noun.",
          "der Mann → des Mann(es): Das Auto des Mannes",
          "",
          "EXAMPLES:",
          "das Auto des Mannes (the man's car)",
          "das Buch des Kindes (the child's book)",
          "",
          "GENITIVE PREPOSITIONS:",
          "wegen (because of), trotz (despite)",
          "während (during), statt (instead of)",
          "",
          "Modern German often uses von + DAT instead"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 33"
      }
