    "title": "LESSON 35: PASSIVE VOICE",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "Passive = focus on ACTION, not who does it:",
          "",
          "PRESENT PASSIVE:",
          "STRUCTURE: werden + past participle",
          "",
          "Das Paket wird geschickt.",
          "(The package is being sent)",
          "",
          "PAST PASSIVE:",
          "STRUCTURE: wurde + past participle",
          "",
          "Das Paket wurde geschickt.",
          "(The package was sent)",
          "",
          "These are the most common passive forms.",
          "Very common in formal/business German."
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 35"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "PERFECT PASSIVE:",
          "STRUCTURE: ist + past participle + worden",
          "",
          "Das Paket ist geschickt worden.",
          "(The package has been sent)",
          "",
          "'worden' is the passive form of 'geworden'.",
          "In passive perfect, always use 'worden'.",
          "",
          "WHO DOES IT (optional):",
          "Add: von + person in dative",
          "",
          "Das Paket wird vom Chef geschickt.",
          "(The package is sent by the boss)",
          "",
          "vom = von + dem (by the)"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
